h1. logback-plotmachine a logback appender for PlotMachine

h2. Introduction

logback-plotmachine is a "logback":logback-link appender for "PlotMachine":plot-link.
The appender sends HTTP calls to a "PlotMachine":plot-link server for every log Event.
It uses the Logger name as the name and the message as the value.

h2. Example:

<pre>
public class MyClass {
  Logger logger  = LoggerFactory.getLogger("UpdateTime");
  
  public void myMethod() {
 
    // long time = ... get the time
    long time = 10;
    logger.info(time);
  }
}
</pre>

<pre>
<configuration scan="false" debug="false">
  <appender name="plotmachine" class="me.shimi.logback.PlotMachineAppender">
    <ApiUrl>http://mydomain/PlotMachine/api/monitor/data/add?</ApiUrl>
  </appender>
  <root level="INFO">
    <appender-ref ref="plotmachine" />
  </root>
</configuration>
</pre>

The appender will make HTTP call to <pre>http://mydomain/PlotMachine/api/monitor/data/add?name=UpdateTime&value=10</pre>

h2. Dependencies

* "logback":logback-link
* "SLF4J":slf4j-link
* "netty":netty-link
* "async-http-client":async-link

[plot-link]http://plotmachine.org
[logback-link]http://logback.qos.ch
[slf4j-link]http://www.slf4j.org
[netty-link]http://www.jboss.org/netty
[async-link]http://github.com/sonatype/async-http-client